Description: We are a new company that is looking to start a wireless ISP.

The world is changing, rural areas are being left behind. Speeds will range up to 150mbps which will compete with current fiber services, but wireless, Thus the rollout cost will be reduced and maintenance will be significantly reduced. We have a fully viable business plan and we are looking to improve it as the days pass. We are looking to provide the best possible customer service, and quality and still make a significant profit. As there are so many that are growing tired of constant let downs by rural ISPs, spotty service, and many are still stuck with dial - up or satellite internet which is extremely restricted and latency is very high. With our wireless system, speeds are faster and latency lower than existing DSL and Cable technologies currently available in the United States.

Full Description: Strain Systems Inc. was established in 2008 with the name Kistler Sensors to bring to market Mr. Kistler’s latest invention, the StrainCell™ sensor. The patented instrument results from his long-held vision to solve a persistent problem in the silo-weighing industry: the issue of temperature-induced errors in readings.  The StrainCell, which installs with a single bolt to the exterior surface of silos, compensates for temperature-related errors during expansion or contraction to ensure highly accurate weight and level measurement of bulk storage materials. By measuring in two directions and mechanically amplifying deflections and distortions, it improves upon the accuracy and reliability of all previous bolt-on strain-measurement inventions.
